The sentence "Mängden av vattnet kan man dessutom variera, för hur mycket man vill få ut för tillfället." can be analyzed with the following dependency tree representation:

```
[
    (1, Mängden, 2),
    (2, av, 3),
    (3, vattnet, 1),
    (4, kan, 5),
    (5, man, 6),
    (6, dessutom, 8),
    (7, variera, 4),
    (8, för, 12),
    (9, hur, 10),
    (10, mycket, 12),
    (11, man, 10),
    (12, vill, 7),
    (13, få, 12),
    (14, ut, 13),
    (15, för, 17),
    (16, tillfället, 15),
    (17, ., 0)
]
```

In this structure:
- Each tuple consists of the token index, the token itself, and the index of its head token.
- The head token for the root of the dependency tree is 'kan', which governs several other tokens and phrases in the sentence. 
- Punctuation is included as part of the token list at the end.